Bliss Toolkit v2.2.2
Jonathan Vasquez <jon@xyinn.org>
2-BSD

Designed for Gentoo Linux

These are a set of scripts that facilitates installing Gentoo Linux on your computer.

Included scripts:

1. 'toostrap' - Asks you which Gentoo stage you want, (optional) downloads
   it with the corresponding latest portage snapshot. It then extracts it into the
   target directory.
2. 'extlinux-install' - Installs the extlinux bootloader to the passed drive
3. 'toochroot' - Cleanly chroots into the target directory.

For more information/instructions check the USAGE file.
